==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Disrobe
<hw>Dis*robe"</hw> <pr>(?; see <er>Dis-</er>)</pr>, <pos>v. t. &
i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Disrobed</conjf>
<pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Disrobing</conjf>.]</vmorph> <def>To divest of a robe; to
undress; figuratively, to strip of covering; to divest of that which
clothes or decorates; <as>as, autumn <ex>disrobes</ex> the fields of
verdure</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Two great peers were <qex>disrobed</qex> of their glory.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir H. Wotton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Disrober</ent>⟦br⟧
